Title: SURF 3 FWV 2.0.6 will not install, being saying installing for 20 hours
Description:
SURF 3 FWV 2.0.6 will not install, being saying installing for 20 hours

Instruction to install Flight Weather Viewer app:

On the S3/Surface 3

Connect to WIFI, make sure the checkbox next to "Connect automatically" is checked.
Select VMWare AirWatch Agent from the start screen, or from the App list under the letter "V".
Note: Access the App List by tapping on the 4 lines in the lower left corner of the start screen.
Select the Install, Update or Reinstall button next to Delta Flight Weather Viewer.
If FWV 2.0.6 version is not in the VMWare AirWatch Agent catalog, open Incident Ticket to Crew-FOPeLink.
Tap Install on the Confirm Installation pop-up window
Once you see the Green banner – “Your request to install was received” your tablet is in queue to receive the update.
Close the VMWare AirWatch Agent and return to the Start Screen ("Processing" indicator will remain until app has completed install and the catalog screen is refreshed).
Wait as Delta Flight Weather Viewer installs in the background.
If FWV does not appear on start screen, check the Apps list.
If found in the Apps list, press and hold the Flight Weather Viewer app icon, then select pin to start.
If unable to resolve, open incident to Crew-FlightOpsBusinessSupport

Title: GE BladePlot program needed to be installed on a workstation
Description:
All,

After spending hours trying to obtain the GE BladePlot program I now have it loaded.

If anyone else needs the GE BladePlot program loaded on their laptops here is the procedure to follow.

I contacted the Help Desk and had them generate a Trouble ticket for a Field Engineer to Install the GE Blade plot Program. I also provided the Field Engineer the below information so they would know where to pull the program from since they don’t readily have this information.

Ed Suttner is the DT guy that normally handle’s this but he has been off, the above process was very simple after doing all the leg work.

There are two folders on \\QATLW7TOBO30.cfdelta.cfrl.delta.com\C$, GE Blade Plot and HP Mobile Printer.

A network drive can be mapped using CFDELTA\InstallApp, password Windows7.

The two folders need to be copied to Paul's machine.  I copy them to C:\LocalFiles.  Admin rights are needed to install both apps.  I believe the Mobile Printer needs to be attached during the installation of the software for it.  The Mobile Printer is in St. Louis, so we may need to wait until Paul has access to the Mobile Printer for its software to be successfully installed.

Field Ops or ODS can do this.

Subject: RE: RAD install issue IM2895138 XATLCAMP10498


Old issue:
Parameter issues       Exiting without running
Program Name:          c:\esd\dist\rad_win\v8.5.4.20\Rad85_Installer8.exe
User ID:               SYSTEM
Computer:              XATLCAMP10498
OS:                    win7_64
Time/Date =            Thu 1/26/2017 5:07:45 PM
Time/Date =            Thu 1/26/2017 5:07:45 PM
strLoggedOnUser      = 327851
Param2               = install
(404)Aborting due to user logon: 327851

Rad will not install if the user is logged in: physically, via rdp or via dameware.  It’s compounded if the user has ‘broken’ a connection with the system without fully logging out first, they are still logged into the system and that causes problems with the install.  It also won’t install via Radia if a manual install was previously done to the system.  There’s been some previous issues that looks like someone may have taken it upon themselves to work outside the system and that looks to have compounded the problems.

Thing is there appears to have been some hand manipulations or something else done via non-radia methods to the install.  The installer is incapable to dealing with whatever has been done in the past to the system outside of the approved methods.

There are only 2 recovery options unless Jason has some means: first is to fully remove RAD including unentitled it via active directory and do a Radia connect.  Once that’s done, do a full cleanup of the system to remove every last remnant of RAD  then with a prior reboot, system online overnight and no one logged in,  let radia install the app and hope all remnants are gone from the system.  Second option is to reimage the system and let everything go in fresh.

There is no verify or repair on RAD.  It’s an all or nothing scenario – either it works or it doesn’t and there’s no fix other than getting it ‘all’ off and starting over from a clean slate.

Sorry – that’s the nature of this particular application.

Title: office 2013 installed, excel won't open
Description:
"There was a problem sending the command to the program"
Issue started as soon as 2013 was installed this morning and Excel hasnt' worked properly since the install.
Open the Microsoft Office program and open its Options window. Click on Office ORB or FILE menu present in the ribbon and then click on Options.
2. Now go to Advanced tab and scroll down to bottom. You'll find "Ignore other applications that use Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE)" option present in General section.
3. Make sure its unchecked. If its enabled in your system, disable it by unchecking the checkbox.
4. Apply changes and restart Office program. It should fix the problem.
PS: If the option is not enabled, first enable the option and then restart the Office program. Now again disable the option and then again restart the Office program. It should fix the problem.
SOLUTION 2:
If the above mentioned solution doesn't work for you, try following method. Basically we are going to re-associate Office program as default application to open the filetype:
1. Right-click on the Office file and select "Open with" option.
2. If you are using Windows 7 or earlier Windows versions, click on Browse button.
3. Now go to "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\Office..." folder in Browse dialog box and select the correct EXE file. For example, if you are trying to open .xlsx file, select EXCEL.EXE file. If you are trying to open .docx file, select WINWORD.EXE file.
Make sure "Always use this application for this file type" or similar option is enabled in Open with window.

Name: EDWIN CORDES
Title: Install Jepp FD Pro
Description:
Install Jepp FD Pro
Connect to the internet by choosing an available WiFi network, ensuring the checkbox next to “Connect automatically” is selected and select Connect.


On the Start screen, select the VMWare AirWatch Agent (App Catalog) or select VMWare AirWatch Agent from the App list under the letter “V”.


Select Apps option
Locate Jeppesen FliteDeck Pro version 8.5.457 then select Install, Installed or Update button
Select Install at the “Confirm Installation” pop-up
Once you receive the “Your request to install was received!” green pop-up, immediately close the VMWare AirWatch Agent
Return to the Start screen by swiping from the top edge to the bottom of the EFB screen. Wait at the Start Screen as the app updates.
The app has successfully updated when the app tile displays 8.5 in the lower left corner of the tile.


Note: Depending on your Wi-Fi connection, it may take up to 30 minutes for the app to install. Please note that after a restart or signing in and signing out, the app will appear under the letter “J” in the app list instead of the letter “F”.

Once the app tile displays 8.5, select the tile to open the app.
On startup, confirm that the app displays “Jeppesen 8.5 Update 1”


If you receive a pop-up to allow FliteDeck access to your location, select No. If you do not receive a pop-up, please disregard this step.


Once the app is open, you may also verify that the update is complete by selecting the App Settings icon in the upper right corner of the app and scrolling down to “Account Info” to confirm that the Build displays 8.5.457.0.
Solution:
Install Jepp FD Pro
Connect to the internet by choosing an available WiFi network, ensuring the checkbox next to “Connect automatically” is selected and select Connect.


On the Start screen, select the VMWare AirWatch Agent (App Catalog) or select VMWare AirWatch Agent from the App list under the letter “V”.


Select Apps option
Locate Jeppesen FliteDeck Pro version 8.5.457 then select Install, Installed or Update button
Select Install at the “Confirm Installation” pop-up
Once you receive the “Your request to install was received!” green pop-up, immediately close the VMWare AirWatch Agent
Return to the Start screen by swiping from the top edge to the bottom of the EFB screen. Wait at the Start Screen as the app updates.
The app has successfully updated when the app tile displays 8.5 in the lower left corner of the tile.


Note: Depending on your Wi-Fi connection, it may take up to 30 minutes for the app to install. Please note that after a restart or signing in and signing out, the app will appear under the letter “J” in the app list instead of the letter “F”.

Once the app tile displays 8.5, select the tile to open the app.
On startup, confirm that the app displays “Jeppesen 8.5 Update 1”


If you receive a pop-up to allow FliteDeck access to your location, select No. If you do not receive a pop-up, please disregard this step.


Once the app is open, you may also verify that the update is complete by selecting the App Settings icon in the upper right corner of the app and scrolling down to “Account Info” to confirm that the Build displays 8.5.457.0.
